args:
Now it is Renee's turn to face her weakness.
According to Arctos, the key is in learning from
the forest. But although the party searches for
the answer in the woods, they are unable to find
it. When night finally falls, the group decides
to gather up forest ingredients for dinner.
Lay it on us, Coach! What's the next\nphase of your training program?
The next stage is where we train you!
Teamwork is the key to your smithing,\nand YOU, Renee, are the linchpin of\nthis particular team!
Hee hee! I suppose my role IS\npretty important.
I mean, not only do I cool the metal,\nbut I also clean up coals and whatnot.\nI've got OODLES of responsibilities!

Hey, I am NOT a gofer, you jerk!
I'm a jill-of-all-trades who can do
any blacksmithing task required!
Or, um, that's the plan, anyway.
But if I'm gonna be the best blacksmith\never, I can't have a single weakness\nin my game. Not one!
That's what ol' Coach likes to hear!\n...But hearing it don't mean squat if\nyou don't overcome your weakness.
You expect me to just TELL you?!\nThat's not how the program works!
Oh, come oooon! At least give me\na little hint or whatever!
Your hint...is the forest.\nLEARN FROM THE TREES!
That is SO not a hint!
Come on, Sis—let's believe in Coach\nand see what we can figure out.
Hell, I bet just the act of thinking about it\nlike this has some kind of deeper meaning.
I guess that's how it was for you, huh?
Okay, well, if I'm gonna walk around a\ndumb forest all day, I guess I'll start...\noooooover...there! Byeeeee!
Whoa, slow down! You can't just run into\nthe woods all alone—they're dangerous!

Maybe we'll come along to keep you
company. Oh, and if you see anything
that seems like it might be important
to your training, just let us know.

I am trying to bear in mind the coach's
admonition to learn from the woods,
and yet I see only the usual amount of
trees, dirt, and...bugs.
I think I may have found something...

See, the way I see it, I have so much
blacksmith talent oozing out of me
that my weakness has to be related
to some OTHER thing.
It means I have to be even MORE\ndazzling and radiant than ever!
So even during the harshest smithing\njob, I'll be as graceful as this flower.\n...Isn't that right, Coach?!
Uh oh. That's totally NOT right, is it?
You are really something sometimes, Sis.
Hee hee! Which is what we love about her.
Okay, fine—didn't hit a home run my first\ntime up to bat. That's fine! I'll try again!
Hey, so I don't wanna ruin this special\nmoment or nothin', but if I don't eat\nsoon, I think I'm gonna keel over.
It IS getting pretty late. Maybe we should\nstop for the day and set up camp.
Unfortunately I thought we would only\nbe gone for the day, and did not bring\nalong any dinner supplies.
So I gotta go to bed without dinner?\nWhat in a hog's fresh hell is THIS?!

Fortunately for us—and it seems Ranzal
in particular—the woods should provide
more than enough ingredients for us to
put together a simple repast.
It's nearly dark, ya dope, and you're\nrunnin' off without any light at all!\n...Here, take this torch.
Everyone who's going to look for food,\ngrab a torch and let's go!
